      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Sept 21 State of the Art column in Circuits section on WordPerfect software</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State of the Art column in Circuits on Sept. 21 about Word Perfect software referred incorrectly to the program used in the New York attorney general's office. It is WordPerfect; the office used Microsoft Word in 1998, when the states' antitrust suit against Microsoft was written there.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The State of the Art column in Circuits on Sept. 21 about Word Perfect software referred incorrectly to the program used in the New York attorney general's office. It is WordPerfect; the office used Microsoft Word in 1998, when the states' antitrust suit against Microsoft was written there.</p>
      </block>
